---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import HeroSection from '../components/HeroSection.astro';
---

<Layout title="About Opal Design LLC">
  <Header />
  <main>
    <HeroSection
      title="Designing Calm. Clearing Chaos. Quietly Powerful."
      description="Welcome to Opal Design, a business built not out of perfection but necessity, grit, and quiet rebellion."
    />
    
    <section class="py-16 bg-white dark:bg-gray-800">
      <div class="container-custom">
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center mb-24">
          <div>
            <span class="inline-block px-4 py-1 rounded-full bg-secondary-100 dark:bg-secondary-900 text-secondary-600 dark:text-secondary-300 font-medium text-sm mb-4">
              Our Origin Story 🐾
            </span>
             <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-6">A Start at the Kitchen Table</h2>
            <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 mb-4">
              We began as a simple idea: What if support felt like exhaling? What if paperwork, logistics, and life admin weren’t so overwhelming?
            </p>
            <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 mb-4">
              Founded by someone who’s been in the thick of burnout, disorganization, and systems that don’t feel built for real people, Opal Design LLC was created to do things differently. Not louder. Not faster. But kinder, sharper, and more intuitive.
            </p>
            <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 mb-4">
              Opal Design started at a kitchen table cluttered with unopened mail, unanswered emails, and half-finished forms. It wasn’t pretty but it was honest.
            </p>
            <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">
               "The help people need isn’t flashy. It’s dependable. Gentle. Effective." From those early days grew a service-first company centered on relief and results. We don’t just organize. We clear paths. We fix things. And we do it without judgment.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="rounded-lg overflow-hidden shadow-xl">
            <img src="https://cdn.pixabay.com/photo/2015/10/31/21/31/bookkeeper-1016299_1280.jpg" alt="Sassify Team" class="w-full h-auto" />
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="mb-24">
          <div class="text-center mb-12">
            <span class="inline-block px-4 py-1 rounded-full bg-secondary-100 dark:bg-secondary-900 text-secondary-600 dark:text-secondary-300 font-medium text-sm mb-4">
              What We Believe 💬
            </span>
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-4">Guiding Principles</h2>
            <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
              Our values shape every interaction and service.
            </p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-8">
            <div class="card p-6 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-2">Respectful Support</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">
                Everyone deserves support that doesn’t feel condescending.
              </p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="card p-6 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-2">Simplicity First</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">
                Complex tasks deserve simple help.
              </p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="card p-6 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-2">Overwhelm Is a Signal</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">
                Being “too overwhelmed” isn’t a flaw. It’s a signal.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="card p-6 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-2">Real Magic</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">
                Magic doesn’t always look like glitter. Sometimes, it’s a form submitted on time.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="mb-24">
          <div class="text-center mb-12">
            <span class="inline-block px-4 py-1 rounded-full bg-secondary-100 dark:bg-secondary-900 text-secondary-600 dark:text-secondary-300 font-medium text-sm mb-4">
              What We Offer 🛠️
            </span>
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-4">Support for Real Life</h2>
            <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
              Opal Design isn’t just a vibe, it’s a service ecosystem for people who need help getting life back in order:
            </p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-8">
            <div class="card p-6 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 text-center">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-2">Form Help &amp; Application Support</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">
                From housing to visas to job portals, we make it make sense.
              </p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="card p-6 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 text-center">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-2">Personal Fixer Services</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">
                Catch up on inboxes, documents and errands quietly, without shame.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="card p-6 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 text-center">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-2">Travel Concierge for Real People</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">
                Travel planning that doesn’t assume you love airports or have energy to spare.
              </p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="card p-6 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 text-center">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-2">Notary Services (Coming Soon)</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">
                Official, mobile, and painless.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="text-center">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-4">Why “Opal”? 💎</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 mb-8 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
            Opals are beautiful, layered, and sensitive to their environment, just like the people we help. They don’t shout for attention, but when you notice them, you feel something real. That’s the energy we bring to every interaction.
          </p>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-4">Our First Employee: Opal the Cat 🐱</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 mb-8 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
            Yes, we have a mascot. Opal the Cat is our calm, cat-like receptionist. She’s part chatbot, part gentle nudge, and all charm. She doesn’t pressure. She purrs. And she points you to help when you need it most.
          </p>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-4">It’s Not That You Can’t Keep Up, It’s That You’ve Been Doing Too Much, Too Long</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 mb-8 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
            Sometimes the world asks more than it gives back. If you're feeling scattered, stuck, or just plain tired, you're not alone. We’re here to lighten the load. Gently. Quietly. In the background, so you can breathe easier and move through your day with a little more space.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout> 
